1 olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 pear
1 carrot
1 packet pork mince
½ tbs soy sauce
½ packet hoisin sauce
1 packet garlic aioli
½ Fresh Chilli
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
½ head cos lettuce

• Finely chop garlic. Shred cos lettuce (see ingredients). Thinly slice pear. Grate carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook the pork mince, breaking it up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and another drizzle of olive oil to pork and cook until fragrant,1 minute.
• Add soy sauce and hoisin sauce (see ingredients) and cook until combined, 1 minute.

• While pork is cooking, add garlic aioli to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine. Set aside.
• Thinly slice long green chilli (if using).
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate for 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Spread a thin layer of aioli over tortillas.
• Top with some cos lettuce, carrot, pear and Vietnamese-style pork.
• Garnish with chilli to serve.